description:
## Parent epic: mulch-632e

Foundational refactor for custom record types. **Zero behavior change** — all existing tests must pass unchanged. Extracts the six built-in record types behind a `TypeDefinition` interface so Phase 2 can plug in custom types via config.

## Goal

Built-ins continue to produce bit-identical output, but their bespoke summary/format/compact/dedup/id logic now lives behind a uniform interface owned by a registry module.

## New files

- `src/registry/type-registry.ts` — exports `TypeDefinition` interface, `TypeRegistry` class with `get(name)`, `enabled()`, `names()`, frozen on build
- `src/registry/builtins.ts` — registers the six built-in `TypeDefinition`s with their existing summary/format/compact/dedup/id functions inlined verbatim
- `src/registry/template.ts` — `compileSummaryTemplate(template)` for `{field}` interpolation (used by Phase 2; landed here so the registry shape is final)

## TypeDefinition interface

```ts
interface TypeDefinition {
  name: string;
  kind: "builtin" | "custom";
  required: readonly string[];
  optional: readonly string[];
  dedupKey: string | "content_hash";
  idKey: string;
  summary: (record: ExpertiseRecord) => string;
  extractsFiles: boolean;
  filesField: string;
  compact: "keep_latest" | "concat" | "merge_outcomes" | "manual";
  sectionTitle: string;
  ajvSchema: Record<string, unknown>;
  formatMarkdown: (records: ExpertiseRecord[], full: boolean) => string;
  formatCompactLine: (record: ExpertiseRecord) => string;
  formatXml: (record: ExpertiseRecord) => string[];
}
```

## Files affected (delegations only — no logic changes)

- `src/utils/expertise.ts:42-65` — `generateRecordId` delegates to `registry.get(r.type).idKey`
- `src/utils/expertise.ts:138-179` — `findDuplicate` dispatches via `registry.get(type).dedupKey`
- `src/utils/format.ts:148-163` — `getRecordSummary` delegates to `def.summary(r)`
- `src/utils/format.ts:73-135` (markdown), `184-207` (compact), `444-513` (xml), `534-614` (plain) — iterate `registry.enabled()` and call `def.formatMarkdown` / `def.formatCompactLine` / `def.formatXml`
- `src/utils/expertise.ts:260, 305-318` — switch `type_distribution` to `Record<string, number>` seeded from `registry.names()`
- `src/cli.ts` — initialize and freeze the registry at startup, expose via module-level singleton

## AJV caching

AJV is currently re-compiled per command in `src/commands/doctor.ts:109`, `src/commands/record.ts:845`, `src/commands/compact.ts:6`, `src/commands/validate.ts:19`. As part of this phase, cache the compiled validator on the registry. Otherwise Phase 2's dynamic schema would compile-per-record on large JSONLs.

## Test strategy

- All existing tests pass unchanged
- Add unit tests for `TypeRegistry` (get, enabled, names, frozen)
- Add a snapshot test: format the same record set with old code path vs. new — bit-identical output

## Risks

- `RecordType` union loosening ripples through ~15 files. Keep `RecordType` as the literal `BuiltinRecordType` alias here; Phase 2 widens to `string`.

## Acceptance

- `bun test` passes
- `bun run typecheck` passes
- `bun run lint` passes
- No behavior change observable from CLI (manual smoke: `ml prime`, `ml record`, `ml search`, `ml status`, `ml doctor`)
